    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a comparative narrative. It starts with a high-level overview, then uses a toggle to let users switch between a 'Generative AI' view and an 'Agentic AI' view. Each view presents a layered breakdown of the respective tech stack. This is followed by new, detailed sections on Use Cases, Risks & Challenges, and Future Trends, each with interactive elements like accordions to manage the density of information. This structure was chosen to guide the user from a high-level comparison to deeper, thematic explorations, making the comprehensive research digestible within a single page. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: Comprehensive analysis of Generative vs. Agentic AI. Goal: Present a deep-dive comparison covering stacks, applications, risks, and future outlook. Viz/Presentation Method: Interactive cards, toggle switch, accordions for detailed text, and multiple charts (radar for complexity, doughnut for use cases, bar for risk profiles). Interaction: The main toggle switches between core stack views. Accordions in new sections allow users to expand topics of interest without being overwhelmed. Charts provide quick visual summaries. Justification: This layered approach—toggle for broad comparison, accordions for depth—is ideal for a content-rich report. It respects user attention by keeping the initial view clean while offering easy access to extensive details. New charts help visualize abstract concepts from the research. Library/Method: Chart.js for all charts due to its versatility and ease of use. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
